This paper is about multi-person pose estimation using a novel single-stage model. The proposed model is based on CNNs and uses a structured pose representation to directly predict poses for multiple persons in a single stage. This work involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as image processing and machine learning (ML) algorithms. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel representation and model architecture, which involves ML techniques such as deep learning and optimization. Hence, it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves experiments on benchmark datasets, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.RO (Robotics). Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, and cs.RO, in that order.
